sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User/CI
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Operator as kuberay-operator<br/>opendatahub namespace
    participant Kubelet as kubelet<br/>10250/TCP HTTPS
    participant Registry as Container Registry<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant HeadPod as Ray Head Pod<br/>6379, 8265, 10001
    participant WorkerPod as Ray Worker Pod<br/>Dynamic ports
    participant S3 as S3/Object Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+

    Note over User,S3: Flow 1: RayCluster Creation and Lifecycle Management

    User->>K8sAPI: POST RayCluster CR<br/>Auth: kubeconfig credentials
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: Watch Event<br/>TLS 1.2+ ServiceAccount Token

    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Pods, Services<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token

    K8sAPI->>Kubelet: Schedule Ray Head Pod<br/>10250/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+<br/>Auth: Node certificate

    Kubelet->>Registry: Pull Ray image<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+<br/>Auth: Image pull secret
    Registry-->>Kubelet: Ray container image

    Kubelet-->>HeadPod: Start Ray Head (GCS + Dashboard)

    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Worker Pods<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    K8sAPI->>Kubelet: Schedule Ray Workers
    Kubelet-->>WorkerPod: Start Ray Workers

    WorkerPod->>HeadPod: Connect to GCS<br/>6379/TCP TCP plaintext<br/>Auth: None

    Note over User,S3: Flow 2: Ray Job Submission via Client

    User->>HeadPod: Submit Ray Job<br/>10001/TCP Ray Protocol<br/>Encryption: None<br/>Auth: None

    HeadPod->>HeadPod: Ray GCS<br/>6379/TCP internal

    HeadPod->>WorkerPod: Distribute Tasks<br/>Dynamic/TCP plaintext<br/>Auth: None

    WorkerPod->>S3: Load Training Data<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+<br/>Auth: AWS IAM/Access Key
    S3-->>WorkerPod: Data artifacts

    WorkerPod-->>HeadPod: Task Results<br/>Dynamic/TCP plaintext
    HeadPod-->>User: Job Complete

    Note over User,S3: Flow 3: Monitoring and Metrics Collection

    participant Prometheus as Prometheus
    participant Dashboard as Ray Dashboard UI<br/>8265/TCP HTTP
    participant Ingress as Ingress Controller

    Prometheus->>Operator: Scrape /metrics<br/>8080/TCP HTTP plaintext<br/>Auth: None
    Prometheus->>HeadPod: Scrape /metrics<br/>8080/TCP HTTP plaintext<br/>Auth: None

    User->>Ingress: Access Dashboard<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+<br/>Auth: via Ingress
    Ingress->>HeadPod: Forward to Dashboard<br/>8265/TCP HTTP plaintext<br/>Auth: None
    HeadPod-->>Ingress: Dashboard UI
    Ingress-->>User: HTTPS Response

    Note over User,S3: Flow 4: KubeRay API Server (Optional)

    participant Client as External Client
    participant APIServer as kuberay-apiserver<br/>8888/8887

    Client->>APIServer: Create RayCluster<br/>8888/TCP HTTP<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (optional)
    APIServer->>K8sAPI: Create RayCluster CR<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>APIServer: CR Created
    APIServer-->>Client: Success Response

    Client->>APIServer: gRPC Request<br/>8887/TCP gRPC/HTTP2<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (optional)
    APIServer->>K8sAPI: Kubernetes Operations<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    K8sAPI-->>APIServer: Response
    APIServer-->>Client: gRPC Response
